      "isVppDeviceBasedLicensingEnabled": true,
      "releaseNotes": "1. Supports direct connection to Yuexingtong X4 for lightweight file management (Beta).\nThis is an upgraded version of the original “Send to Device” feature. It now supports batch sending of files from your phone to the device, as well as renaming/moving and deleting files. You can also import files into DianMo directly from other apps via the share action.\n2. Added controls for adjusting font weight and character/line spacing for TTF fonts (Beta).\nAfter importing a tweaked TTF, this helps alleviate the limitation of the native Kindle reader, where character and line spacing cannot be finely adjusted.\n3. Simplified/Traditional Chinese glyph conversion now supports conversion for 2,800+ commonly used Simplified Chinese characters.\n4. Attempted to fix several potential bugs on older versions of iOS, and made various improvements to the UI and overall interaction experience.",
      "version": "1.4",
      "wrapperType": "software",
      "currency": "USD",
      "description": "Convert your favorite fonts for your portable e-ink readers — right from your phone.\nDotInk lets you easily transform .ttf fonts into .bin fonts optimized for e-ink devices, without needing a computer.\n\nKey Features:\n1. Use system fonts or import external .ttf font files.\n2. Customize character spacing, line height, size, and weight for better readability on your e-ink display.\n3. Preview font rendering in real time — closely simulating the actual e-ink device display.\n4. Supports multiple portable e-ink readers, including XTEINK X4, MoFei 3.7, and WuDaDa·XiaoMo.\n5. Added support for interaction with e-ink devices, such as pushing fonts directly to the device. (Currently supported: ReadStar X4)\n\nDesigned for readers, creators, and developers who value clarity and simplicity.\n\nThank you to all our early supporters — we welcome your feedback, ideas, and suggestions!",
